HEADWORD: Diapedesis
<hw>Di`a*pe*de"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ a leaping or oozing through, fr. <?/ to leap through;
<grk>dia`</grk> through + <?/ to leap.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The
passage of the corpuscular elements of the blood from the blood vessels
into the surrounding tissues, without rupture of the walls of the blood
vessels.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

